I want to thank you for your support. But more importantly thank you for voting! Your vote is your voice: raise it loud.   Now let's go take back our democracy! Que esperas?   Go out there and vote like your life depends on it because it does.
Join the millions of Americans that have already voted: 🗳 Drop your ballot off at a drop box today.  🏢 Or vote in person by going to a voting center. 😷 But please don't forget your mask!

Joe believes in science. He has a plan to shut down the virus. He understands that we as Latinos are disproportionately affected by COVID-19. Alguien que de veras va a luchar por nosotros that leader is @JoeBiden.

I have never stopped fighting for you and your family in Congress and I don't plan on stopping now.  But it’s not just about me. This election is about ALL of us. And that means we need to elect a new President. It’s absolutely clear: we must elect @JoeBiden.

If you send me back to Congress I will:  🔴 keep fighting for working families to have access to universal healthcare  ⚪️ protect a woman's right to choose and  🔵 make sure we work to create jobs in our communities.
I am also on the ballot. I’m running for reelection to the United States Congress. I want to keep kicking some ass for the working class and keep fighting for YOU.
We are just days away from the most consequential election of our lifetimes. And Californians are already voting. Truth and democracy are on the ballot!

I can't believe I even have to say this but here it goes.   The President is just plain wrong.   We *do* need to be concerned about #COVID19.   This virus is serious so we must be too. Wash your hands and wear a damn mask!
Go to https://t.co/au4oYV8jg3 and make your voting plan today.  Let's work together to spread the word and show up -- early by mail or in person at the polls -- and we can give Trump the 🥾.

To my Latino brothers and sisters here’s your friendly Friday reminder… we can be the ones to give President Trump the 🥾 boot! But we have to VOTE like our lives depend on it. Because they do. You can vote early by mail or in person on November 3.

So let me get this straight.   The President First Lady and senior WH staff are diagnosed with COVID.   The WH didn’t call.  The Speaker of the House and the Democratic presidential nominee just found out about it on TV like the rest of America?

President Trump and the First Lady have tested positive for COVID19. They will have access to the best medical care in the world and I wish him them both a full and quick recovery.   But this is a stark reminder...  COVID is not a hoax. It is very real.   Wear. A. Damn. Mask.
